data.value: Patient's Bill of Rights and Responsibilities

data.name: PatientResponsible2
data.value: 2. Give correct historical information about his/her old diseases to the doctor.

data.name: PatientResponsible3
data.value: 3. Inform the responible medical staff if he/she can't Adhere to the medical instructions.

data.name: PatientResponsible4
data.value: 4. Adherence to his/ her appointments and call if want to cancel or not attend.

data.name: PatientResponsible5
data.value: 5. Adherence to the hospital's smoke-free policy.

data.name: PatientRight1
data.value: 1. Be informed about their rights and responsibilities.

data.name: PatientRight10
data.value: 10. Be protected from physical and verbal assault.

data.name: PatientRight11
data.value: 11. Appropriate assessment and management of pain.

data.name: PatientRight12
data.value: 12. Participate in their care including making decisions or asking questions about care and seeking a second opinion without fear or compromising care.

data.name: PatientRight14
data.value: 14. Consent to surgery, high risk treatments and procedures anesthesia, and use of blood and blood products, after receiving adequate information.

data.name: PatientRight15
data.value: 15. Refuse or discontinue treatment and be informed of the consequences if the decision, responsibilities related to such decision and available care and treatment alternatives.

data.name: PatientRight16
data.value: 16. Respectful and compassionate care at the end of life.

data.name: PatientRight17
data.value: 17. Be fully informed about clinical research which they agree to participate in, and the right to refuse or withdraw consent without affecting the care provided.

data.name: PatientRight18
data.value: 18. Be informed about donation and transplantation of organs and other tissues as per hospital policy.

data.name: PatientRight19
data.value: 19. Voice a complaint about care or hospital services and have the complaint investigated and resolved whenever is possible.

data.name: PatientRight2
data.value: 2. Be informed of the services provided in the hospital.

data.name: PatientRight20
data.value: 20. Have their possessions protected once the hospital assumes responsibilities for protecting possessions or when the patient cannot resume responsibility.

data.name: PatientRight21
data.value: 21. Receive a report on their medical condition according to hospital regulations.

data.name: PatientRight3
data.value: 3. Providing a safe environment for him in all hospital facilities

data.name: PatientRight4
data.value: 4. Know the identities of the physicians and the other practitioners responsible for his/ her care.

data.name: PatientRight5
data.value: 5. Be treated with respect and dignity at all times and under all circumstances.

data.name: PatientRight6
data.value: 6. Receive care that is respectful of their values and beliefs (provided that they don’t conflict with Islamic rules).

data.name: PatientRight7
data.value: 7. Respect and maintain their privacy during care and according to their needs.

data.name: PatientRight8
data.value: 8. Have a significant other. Chaperon or a staff member from the same gender be present during physical examination, treatment or procedure.

data.name: PatientRight9
data.value: 9. Maintain confidentiality of all information, communication and records related to the care.
